# BCP 47 language-tag slice v1 — benchmark-grade, trimmed
#
# 15 primary language subtags from the IANA Language Subtag Registry,
# all ISO 639-1 two-letter codes under RFC 5646 §2.2.1. Covers the
# motivating example and a representative spread of EU official
# languages.
#
# Structure:
#   Flat registry: 15 atomic tags, no hierarchy.
#   Partial order on the resource is equality of tags (Table 1 in
#   the paper). Disjointness comes from RFC 5646's registry-uniqueness
#   rule: every primary language subtag identifies a distinct language,
#   so the 15 tags are pairwise disjoint.
#
# Rationale:
#   - de and fr are required for the motivating example
#     (the bcp:de ⊥ bcp:fr Conflict verdict on the language pair).
#   - The remaining 13 give coverage across EU official languages
#     to exercise multi-valued constraints (isAnyOf, isNoneOf)
#     without synthetic entries.
#   - 15 tags matches the GeoNames and DPV slice sizes for
#     cross-resource evaluation balance.
#
# Encoding: each tag is an individual instance of bcp:LanguageTag.
# Unlike the GeoNames and DPV slices, disjointness IS asserted
# (via owl:AllDifferent), because registry uniqueness is a genuine
# RFC 5646 axiom rather than a conservative closure applied at
# evaluation time. This is the resource that gives the motivating
# example its Conflict verdict, per Table 3 in the paper.
#
# BCP 47 does not define official IRIs for subtags; the bcp: prefix
# used here is a pragmatic convention.

@prefix bcp:  <https://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47#> .
@prefix owl:  <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

### Class ###################################################################

bcp:LanguageTag a rdfs:Class ;
    rdfs:label "BCP 47 Language Tag" .

### Primary language tags (ISO 639-1, alphabetised) #########################

bcp:bg a bcp:LanguageTag ;  rdfs:label "Bulgarian"  .
bcp:cs a bcp:LanguageTag ;  rdfs:label "Czech"      .
bcp:da a bcp:LanguageTag ;  rdfs:label "Danish"     .
bcp:de a bcp:LanguageTag ;  rdfs:label "German"     .
bcp:el a bcp:LanguageTag ;  rdfs:label "Greek"      .
bcp:en a bcp:LanguageTag ;  rdfs:label "English"    .
bcp:es a bcp:LanguageTag ;  rdfs:label "Spanish"    .
bcp:fi a bcp:LanguageTag ;  rdfs:label "Finnish"    .
bcp:fr a bcp:LanguageTag ;  rdfs:label "French"     .
bcp:hu a bcp:LanguageTag ;  rdfs:label "Hungarian"  .
bcp:it a bcp:LanguageTag ;  rdfs:label "Italian"    .
bcp:nl a bcp:LanguageTag ;  rdfs:label "Dutch"      .
bcp:pl a bcp:LanguageTag ;  rdfs:label "Polish"     .
bcp:pt a bcp:LanguageTag ;  rdfs:label "Portuguese" .
bcp:sv a bcp:LanguageTag ;  rdfs:label "Swedish"    .

### Registry uniqueness axiom ###############################################
# RFC 5646 §2.2.1: every primary language subtag identifies a distinct
# language. The 15 tags above are therefore pairwise disjoint.

[] a owl:AllDifferent ;
    owl:distinctMembers (
        bcp:bg bcp:cs bcp:da bcp:de bcp:el bcp:en bcp:es bcp:fi
        bcp:fr bcp:hu bcp:it bcp:nl bcp:pl bcp:pt bcp:sv
    ) .